===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[clock]] made of two [[glass]] vessels connected by a narrow passage through which sand flows.
#: {{syn|en|sandglass|sand timer|watch glass}}
#: {{hypo|en|egg timer}}
#: {{ux|en|After each game turn, invert the '''hourglass''' to reset the time limit for the next player.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|title={{w|The Fall of Hyperion: A Dream|The Fall of Hyperion}}|year=1819|author=John Keats|authorlink=John Keats|chapter=[[s:en:The Fall of Hyperion: A Dream#CANTO_I|Canto I]]|passage=The sands of thy short life are spent this hour, / And no hand in the universe can turn / Thy '''hourglass''', if these gummed leaves be burnt / Ere thou canst mount up these immortal steps.}}
# {{lb|en|GUI}} A [[cursor]], often shaped like an hourglass, indicating that the computer is busy.
#: {{syn|en|egg timer}}
#: {{cot|en|beach ball|q=Apple}}
#* '''2002''', ''Maximum PC'' (Winter 2002, page 16)
#*: When I right click the desktop display to check Display Properties, it hangs and shows me only the '''hourglass''' instead of the display menu.

